text: Lynn Snel (born 14 May 1998) is a Dutch karateka from Zaandam. She represents the Netherlands at international competitions. Snel is multiple times Dutch national champion. Snel was not able to qualify for the delayed 2020 Summer Olympics. Despite a poor preparation, Snel won the bronze medal at the 2021 World Karate Championships. It was the first time since 17 years the Netherlands won a medal at the World Championships.
